-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/ARF> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Medium to pale grey mottled, dominantly calcareous, extensively bioturbated, thickly bedded, \"unstriped\" siltstone with thin siltstone laminations."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/BFLS> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Rubbly, massive to nodular limestone-calcrete palaeosol horizons."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CCV> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Acid ash-flow tuff."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CMK> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Mudstone and siltstone, black, graptolitic. Mudstones at the base of the formation are calcareous and contain a shelly fauna. Towards the top of the formation calcareous siltstones contain nodules and thin beds of limestone."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/FYNL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Limestone."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H1002> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "[Obsolete: use KMF, SCH]"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H2128> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "[Obsolete: use CSW]"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H2680> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "[Obsolete: use CEI]"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H3544> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "[Obsolete: use LVT]"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H3966> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "[Obsolete: use CSW]"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H4214> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "[Obsolete: use NAH]"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H4292> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "[Obsolete: use MMG, RDM]"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H4764> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "[Obsolete: use LLNC]"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HGSA> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Sandstone."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HOF> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Laminated silty mudstone. Underlying and overlying units are greywacke sandstones."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/HRG> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Interbedded greywacke, sandstones and siltstones. Underlying and overlying laminated silty mudstone."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/IRE> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Pale to dark grey, massive or thickly bedded limestone, commonly pervasively recrystallised with bedding planes which are either stylotitic or totally obscured; dolomitisation and haematite staining common in the south of the inlier with the limestone becoming cavernous and mottled brown in colour."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LRF> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "[Obsolete: use LWW] Dacitic lapilli tuff."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LSD> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Conglomerates and sandstones with subordinate red and green siltstones and shaly mudstones."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LVV> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "[Obsolete]"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/NAH> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Not defined. NOTE: Details as for Nant-Hir Shales. Name only modified."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/NSH> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "[Obsolete: use NAH]"@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/PYGA> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Spilitic pillow lavas with subordinate pyroclastic bands to the east and central parts of the Cader Idris Range and dominantly pyroclastic rocks to the west. (Correlative of Pen-Y-Gader Group = Upper Basic Volcanic Group)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/RDM> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "[Obsolete] Red siltstones and mudstones with subordinate sandstones. Correlative of Red Marl Group is the Milford Haven Group."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SAM> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Red or green siltstones (marls). Red, sometimes nodular mudstones, very fine- to fine-grained, bright green or purple sandstones and intra-formational conglomerates. (Sandstone and Marl Group = division of Red Marls)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SCH> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Sandstone with subsidiary siliciclastic argillaceous rock."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/UCM> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "[Obsolete: use PUCM, UCMS] Grey mudstone, siltstone and pale grey sandstone interbedded; coal seams common; no mudstones with marine fossils (marine bands) present."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/UMG> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Red, locally nodular, mudstones, fine- to very fine-grained sandstones and intraformational conglomerates: lithology represents fining up sequences (cyclothems)."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/UND> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Uniform succession of sediments consisting generally of ill-sorted, silt-size quartz grains irregularly distributed in a matrix of very fine silt and clay, with subordinate discontinuous units of well-sorted siltstone."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/WIL> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Sandstone."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/YFS> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLithologyDescription> "Sandstone."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CCV> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLowerBoundaryDefinition> "Conformable on sandstones and/or mudstones of undivided Nant Ffrancon Group."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LSD> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasLowerBoundaryDefinition> "Unconformable upon strata of the Borrowdale Volcanic Group."@en .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CEI> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasObsoleteEquivalent> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H2680> .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CSW> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasObsoleteEquivalent> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H2128> .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/CSW> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasObsoleteEquivalent> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H3966> .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/KMF> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasObsoleteEquivalent> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H1002> .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LLNC> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasObsoleteEquivalent> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H4764> .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LVT> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasObsoleteEquivalent> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H3544> .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/NAH> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasObsoleteEquivalent> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H4214> .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/NAH> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasObsoleteEquivalent> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/NSH> .
-<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/RDM> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Lexicon/hasObsoleteEquivalent> <http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/H4292> .
